  emsenn:Method "The method of sociology is critical analysis of social structures and power relations, drawing on specific schools and lineages (Marxism, critical theory, feminism, Black radical tradition, anarchism, etc.) to examine how societies organize themselves and how those arrangements are challenged." ;
  emsenn:Teleology "The goal of sociology is to understand how social order is produced, maintained, and contested — how institutions, power relations, and collective action shape human life." ;
